entities.rdfs:label: Abstract result
entities.rdfs:comment: The base class of validation results, typically not instantiated directly.

entities.rdfs:label: And constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to test whether a value node conforms to all members of a provided list of shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: Blank node
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all blank nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Blank node or IRI
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all blank nodes or IRIs.

entities.rdfs:label: Blank node or literal
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all blank nodes or literals.

entities.rdfs:label: Class constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that each value node is an instance of a given type.

entities.rdfs:label: Closed constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to indicate that focus nodes must only have values for those properties that have been explicitly enumerated via sh:property/sh:path.

entities.rdfs:label: Constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of constraint components.

entities.rdfs:label: Datatype constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the datatype of all value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Disjoint constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that the set of value nodes is disjoint with the the set of nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

entities.rdfs:label: Equals constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that the set of value nodes is equal to the set of nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

entities.rdfs:label: Expression constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a given node expression produces true for all value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Function
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SHACL functions.

entities.rdfs:label: Has-value constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that one of the value nodes is a given RDF node.

entities.rdfs:label: IRI
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all IRIs.

entities.rdfs:label: IRI or literal
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all IRIs or literals.

entities.rdfs:label: In constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to exclusively enumerate the permitted value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Info
entities.rdfs:comment: The severity for an informational validation result.

entities.rdfs:label: Language-in constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to enumerate language tags that all value nodes must have.

entities.rdfs:label: Less-than constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that each value node is smaller than all the nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

entities.rdfs:label: less-than-or-equals constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that every value node is smaller than all the nodes that have the focus node as subject and the value of a given property as predicate.

entities.rdfs:label: Literal
entities.rdfs:comment: The node kind of all literals.

entities.rdfs:label: Max-count constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the maximum number of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Max-exclusive constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a maximum exclusive value.

entities.rdfs:label: Max-inclusive constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a maximum inclusive value.

entities.rdfs:label: Max-length constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the maximum string length of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Min-count constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the minimum number of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Min-exclusive constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a minimum exclusive value.

entities.rdfs:label: Min-inclusive constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the range of value nodes with a minimum inclusive value.

entities.rdfs:label: Min-length constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the minimum string length of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Node constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that all value nodes conform to the given node shape.

entities.rdfs:label: Node kind
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of all node kinds, including sh:BlankNode, sh:IRI, sh:Literal or the combinations of these: sh:BlankNodeOrIRI, sh:BlankNodeOrLiteral, sh:IRIOrLiteral.

entities.rdfs:label: Node-kind constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the RDF node kind of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: Node shape
entities.rdfs:comment: A node shape is a shape that specifies constraint that need to be met with respect to focus nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Not constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that value nodes do not conform to a given shape.

entities.rdfs:label: Or constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the value nodes so that they conform to at least one out of several provided shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: Parameter
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of parameter declarations, consisting of a path predicate and (possibly) information about allowed value type, cardinality and other characteristics.

entities.rdfs:label: Parameterizable
entities.rdfs:comment: Superclass of components that can take parameters, especially functions and constraint components.

entities.rdfs:label: Pattern constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that every value node matches a given regular expression.

entities.rdfs:label: Prefix declaration
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of prefix declarations, consisting of pairs of a prefix with a namespace.

entities.rdfs:label: Property constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that all value nodes conform to the given property shape.

entities.rdfs:label: Property group
entities.rdfs:comment: Instances of this class represent groups of property shapes that belong together.

entities.rdfs:label: Property shape
entities.rdfs:comment: A property shape is a shape that specifies constraints on the values of a focus node for a given property or path.

entities.rdfs:label: Qualified-max-count constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a specified maximum number of value nodes conforms to a given shape.

entities.rdfs:label: Qualified-min-count constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to verify that a specified minimum number of value nodes conforms to a given shape.

entities.rdfs:label: Result annotation
entities.rdfs:comment: A class of result annotations, which define the rules to derive the values of a given annotation property as extra values for a validation result.

entities.rdfs:label: Rule
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SHACL rules. Never instantiated directly.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL ASK executable
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SPARQL executables that are based on an ASK query.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL ASK validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of validators based on SPARQL ASK queries. The queries are evaluated for each value node and are supposed to return true if the given node conforms.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL constraint
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of constraints based on SPARQL SELECT queries.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to define constraints based on SPARQL queries.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL CONSTRUCT executable
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SPARQL executables that are based on a CONSTRUCT query.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL executable
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of resources that encapsulate a SPARQL query.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL function
entities.rdfs:comment: A function backed by a SPARQL query - either ASK or SELECT.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL CONSTRUCT rule
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SHACL rules based on SPARQL CONSTRUCT queries.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL SELECT executable
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SPARQL executables based on a SELECT query.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL SELECT validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of validators based on SPARQL SELECT queries. The queries are evaluated for each focus node and are supposed to produce bindings for all focus nodes that do not conform.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL target
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of targets that are based on SPARQL queries.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL target type
entities.rdfs:comment: The (meta) class for parameterizable targets that are based on SPARQL queries.

entities.rdfs:label: SPARQL UPDATE executable
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SPARQL executables based on a SPARQL UPDATE.

entities.rdfs:label: Severity
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of validation result severity levels, including violation and warning levels.

entities.rdfs:label: Shape
entities.rdfs:comment: A shape is a collection of constraints that may be targeted for certain nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: Target
entities.rdfs:comment: The base class of targets such as those based on SPARQL queries.

entities.rdfs:label: Target type
entities.rdfs:comment: The (meta) class for parameterizable targets.	Instances of this are instantiated as values of the sh:target property.

entities.rdfs:label: A rule based on triple (subject, predicate, object) pattern.
Unique-languages constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to specify that no pair of value nodes may use the same language tag.

entities.rdfs:label: Validation report
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of SHACL validation reports.

entities.rdfs:label: Validation result
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of validation results.

entities.rdfs:label: Validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The class of validators, which provide instructions on how to process a constraint definition. This class serves as base class for the SPARQL-based validators and other possible implementations.

entities.rdfs:label: Violation
entities.rdfs:comment: The severity for a violation validation result.

entities.rdfs:label: Warning
entities.rdfs:comment: The severity for a warning validation result.

entities.rdfs:label: Exactly one constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: A constraint component that can be used to restrict the value nodes so that they conform to exactly one out of several provided shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: alternative path
entities.rdfs:comment: The (single) value of this property must be a list of path elements, representing the elements of alternative paths.

entities.rdfs:label: and
entities.rdfs:comment: RDF list of shapes to validate the value nodes against.

entities.rdfs:label: annotation property
entities.rdfs:comment: The annotation property that shall be set.

entities.rdfs:label: annotation value
entities.rdfs:comment: The (default) values of the annotation property.

entities.rdfs:label: annotation variable name
entities.rdfs:comment: The name of the SPARQL variable from the SELECT clause that shall be used for the values.

entities.rdfs:label: ask
entities.rdfs:comment: The SPARQL ASK query to execute.

entities.rdfs:label: class
entities.rdfs:comment: The type that all value nodes must have.

entities.rdfs:label: closed
entities.rdfs:comment: If set to true then the shape is closed.

entities.rdfs:label: condition
entities.rdfs:comment: The shapes that the focus nodes need to conform to before a rule is executed on them.

entities.rdfs:label: conforms
entities.rdfs:comment: True if the validation did not produce any validation results, and false otherwise.

entities.rdfs:label: construct
entities.rdfs:comment: The SPARQL CONSTRUCT query to execute.

entities.rdfs:label: datatype
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies an RDF datatype that all value nodes must have.

entities.rdfs:label: deactivated
entities.rdfs:comment: If set to true then all nodes conform to this.

entities.rdfs:label: declare
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a resource with its namespace prefix declarations.

entities.rdfs:label: default value
entities.rdfs:comment: A default value for a property, for example for user interface tools to pre-populate input fields.

entities.rdfs:label: description
entities.rdfs:comment: Human-readable descriptions for the property in the context of the surrounding shape.

entities.rdfs:label: detail
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a result with other results that provide more details, for example to describe violations against nested shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: disjoint
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a property where the set of values must be disjoint with the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: entailment
entities.rdfs:comment: An entailment regime that indicates what kind of inferencing is required by a shapes graph.

entities.rdfs:label: equals
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a property that must have the same values as the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: expression
entities.rdfs:comment: The node expression that must return true for the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: filter shape
entities.rdfs:comment: The shape that all input nodes of the expression need to conform to.

entities.rdfs:label: flags
entities.rdfs:comment: An optional flag to be used with regular expression pattern matching.

entities.rdfs:label: focus node
entities.rdfs:comment: The focus node that was validated when the result was produced.

entities.rdfs:label: group
entities.rdfs:comment: Can be used to link to a property group to indicate that a property shape belongs to a group of related property shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: has value
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a value that must be among the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: ignored properties
entities.rdfs:comment: An optional RDF list of properties that are also permitted in addition to those explicitly enumerated via sh:property/sh:path.

entities.rdfs:label: in
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a list of allowed values so that each value node must be among the members of the given list.

entities.rdfs:label: intersection
entities.rdfs:comment: A list of node expressions that shall be intersected.

entities.rdfs:label: inverse path
entities.rdfs:comment: The (single) value of this property represents an inverse path (object to subject).

entities.rdfs:label: label template
entities.rdfs:comment: Outlines how human-readable labels of instances of the associated Parameterizable shall be produced. The values can contain {?paramName} as placeholders for the actual values of the given parameter.

entities.rdfs:label: language in
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a list of language tags that all value nodes must have.

entities.rdfs:label: less than
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a property that must have smaller values than the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: less than or equals
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a property that must have smaller or equal values than the value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: max count
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the maximum number of values in the set of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: max exclusive
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the maximum exclusive value of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: max inclusive
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the maximum inclusive value of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: max length
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the maximum string length of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: message
entities.rdfs:comment: A human-readable message (possibly with placeholders for variables) explaining the cause of the result.

entities.rdfs:label: min count
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the minimum number of values in the set of value nodes.

entities.rdfs:label: min exclusive
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the minimum exclusive value of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: min inclusive
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the minimum inclusive value of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: min length
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the minimum string length of each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: name
entities.rdfs:comment: Human-readable labels for the property in the context of the surrounding shape.

entities.rdfs:label: namespace
entities.rdfs:comment: The namespace associated with a prefix in a prefix declaration.

entities.rdfs:label: node
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the node shape that all value nodes must conform to.

entities.rdfs:label: node kind
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the node kind (e.g. IRI or literal) each value node.

entities.rdfs:label: shape validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The validator(s) used to evaluate a constraint in the context of a node shape.

entities.rdfs:label: nodes
entities.rdfs:comment: The node expression producing the input nodes of a filter shape expression.

entities.rdfs:label: not
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a shape that the value nodes must not conform to.

entities.rdfs:label: object
entities.rdfs:comment: An expression producing the nodes that shall be inferred as objects.

entities.rdfs:label: one or more path
entities.rdfs:comment: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched one or more times.

entities.rdfs:label: optional
entities.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether a parameter is optional.

entities.rdfs:label: or
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a list of shapes so that the value nodes must conform to at least one of the shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: order
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the relative order of this compared to its siblings. For example use 0 for the first, 1 for the second.

entities.rdfs:label: parameter
entities.rdfs:comment: The parameters of a function or constraint component.

entities.rdfs:label: path
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies the property path of a property shape.

entities.rdfs:label: pattern
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a regular expression pattern that the string representations of the value nodes must match.

entities.rdfs:label: predicate
entities.rdfs:comment: An expression producing the properties that shall be inferred as predicates.

entities.rdfs:label: prefix
entities.rdfs:comment: The prefix of a prefix declaration.

entities.rdfs:label: prefixes
entities.rdfs:comment: The prefixes that shall be applied before parsing the associated SPARQL query.

entities.rdfs:label: property
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to its property shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: property validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The validator(s) used to evaluate a constraint in the context of a property shape.

entities.rdfs:label: qualified max count
entities.rdfs:comment: The maximum number of value nodes that can conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: qualified min count
entities.rdfs:comment: The minimum number of value nodes that must conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: qualified value shape
entities.rdfs:comment: The shape that a specified number of values must conform to.

entities.rdfs:label: qualified value shapes disjoint
entities.rdfs:comment: Can be used to mark the qualified value shape to be disjoint with its sibling shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: result
entities.rdfs:comment: The validation results contained in a validation report.

entities.rdfs:label: result annotation
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a SPARQL validator with zero or more sh:ResultAnnotation instances, defining how to derive additional result properties based on the variables of the SELECT query.

entities.rdfs:label: result message
entities.rdfs:comment: Human-readable messages explaining the cause of the result.

entities.rdfs:label: result path
entities.rdfs:comment: The path of a validation result, based on the path of the validated property shape.

entities.rdfs:label: result severity
entities.rdfs:comment: The severity of the result, e.g. warning.

entities.rdfs:label: return type
entities.rdfs:comment: The expected type of values returned by the associated function.

entities.rdfs:label: rule
entities.rdfs:comment: The rules linked to a shape.

entities.rdfs:label: select
entities.rdfs:comment: The SPARQL SELECT query to execute.

entities.rdfs:label: severity
entities.rdfs:comment: Defines the severity that validation results produced by a shape must have. Defaults to sh:Violation.

entities.rdfs:label: shapes graph
entities.rdfs:comment: Shapes graphs that should be used when validating this data graph.

entities.rdfs:label: shapes graph well-formed
entities.rdfs:comment: If true then the validation engine was certain that the shapes graph has passed all SHACL syntax requirements during the validation process.

entities.rdfs:label: source constraint
entities.rdfs:comment: The constraint that was validated when the result was produced.

entities.rdfs:label: source constraint component
entities.rdfs:comment: The constraint component that is the source of the result.

entities.rdfs:label: source shape
entities.rdfs:comment: The shape that is was validated when the result was produced.

entities.rdfs:label: constraint (in SPARQL)
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape with SPARQL constraints.

entities.rdfs:label: subject
entities.rdfs:comment: An expression producing the resources that shall be inferred as subjects.

entities.rdfs:label: suggested shapes graph
entities.rdfs:comment: Suggested shapes graphs for this ontology. The values of this property may be used in the absence of specific sh:shapesGraph statements.

entities.rdfs:label: target
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to a target specified by an extension language, for example instances of sh:SPARQLTarget.

entities.rdfs:label: target class
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to a class, indicating that all instances of the class must conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: target node
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to individual nodes, indicating that these nodes must conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: target objects of
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to a property, indicating that all all objects of triples that have the given property as their predicate must conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: target subjects of
entities.rdfs:comment: Links a shape to a property, indicating that all subjects of triples that have the given property as their predicate must conform to the shape.

entities.rdfs:label: this
entities.rdfs:comment: A node expression that represents the current focus node.

entities.rdfs:label: union
entities.rdfs:comment: A list of node expressions that shall be used together.

entities.rdfs:label: unique languages
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies whether all node values must have a unique (or no) language tag.

entities.rdfs:label: update
entities.rdfs:comment: The SPARQL UPDATE to execute.

entities.rdfs:label: validator
entities.rdfs:comment: The validator(s) used to evaluate constraints of either node or property shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: value
entities.rdfs:comment: An RDF node that has caused the result.

entities.rdfs:label: exactly one
entities.rdfs:comment: Specifies a list of shapes so that the value nodes must conform to exactly one of the shapes.

entities.rdfs:label: zero or more path
entities.rdfs:comment: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched zero or more times.

entities.rdfs:label: zero or one path
entities.rdfs:comment: The (single) value of this property represents a path that is matched zero or one times.
